{
  "texts": [
    "Second, the limited average earnings impacts primarily reflect the overwhelming share of workers reporting no change in earnings due to AI chatbots-rather than large positive and negative effects offsetting each other.",
    "This supports our conclusion from Figures 4 and 5 that AI chatbots have not had significant heterogeneous impacts on workers.",
    "Finally, the fact that virtually 100% of non-adopters report no earnings impact suggests that occupation-wide spillovers are minimal.",
    "Despite broad adoption and changes in work content, AI chatbots do not appear to have shifted equilibrium wages or hours.",
    "Taken together, these self-reported perceptions from front-line workers in the most exposed occupations reinforce our conclusion that AI chatbots have so far had limited impacts on labor markets."
  ]
}